                <h2>What is the Hong Kong Airlines Refund Policy? </h2>
                <p>The Hong Kong airline is well-known for offering consumers a stress-free flying experience. Read on to find out more about <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/hong-kong-airlines-refund-policy.aspx">Hong Kong Airlines' return policy</a>.</p>
                <p>If you cancel within 24 hours of your flight, you will receive a full refund with no restrictions or conditions. The kind of <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/">airline ticket </a>has no influence on the amount of the refund. When cancelling a <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/hong-kong-airlines.aspx">Hong Kong Airlines flight</a> due to the loss of a family member, you must present a copy of the death certificate. </p>
                <p>If your flight is delayed for more than three hours, you are entitled to a full refund. If your flight is delayed due to a natural disaster, such as earthquakes, hurricanes, floods, heavy rain, thunder, or extreme weather, the airline will repay your ticket. </p>
                <h2>FAQs</h2>
                <h3>Can you get a refund from Hong Kong Airlines?</h3>
                <p>Unquestionably. Your refund claim should be legitimate if Hong Kong Airlines cancels your booked flight without a good cause. Using our free calculator, you can determine how much Hong Kong Airlines delay compensation you are entitled to. When filling out our customer verification form, keep your booking reference number available. </p>
                <h3>How can a refund for a reservation paid in cash be obtained? </h3>
                <p>Cash refunds are available at domestic airport counters; however, if the reservation was purchased at our international airport counter, consumers must contact us at customer.relations@goindigo.in for assistance. </p>
                <h3>Are there any extra tax duties for the special fare tickets? </h3>
                <p>Taxes are not included in special fare tickets unless otherwise specified. Taxes and levies are subject to change at any time, and the following is the reference price: Taxes from Hong Kong to China cities are around HK$235; Bali is roughly HK$120. </p>
                <h3>How to purchase tickets for children and infants? </h3>
                <p>Infant Passenger Tickets for children under the age of two are available via the Customer Service Hotline. You can call customer support and ask for help. The Hong Kong Airlines mobile app may be used to purchase child passenger tickets (those under the age of 12. Child passenger tickets, on the other hand, cannot be purchased without an adult is present. </p>
                <h3>Hong Kong has what customs requirements? </h3>
